<http://dx.doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3918.2.8>
    dc:creator "Lisi, Oscar", "Pilato, Giovanni", "Sabella, Giorgio" ;
    dc:date "2015" ;
    dc:title "Two new freshwater eutardigrade species from Sicily" ;
    bibo:endPage "284" ;
    bibo:issue "2" ;
    bibo:journal "Zootaxa" ;
    bibo:startPage "273" ;
    bibo:volume "3918" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232649>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232650>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232651>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232652> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232649>
    dc:description "FIGURE 2. A – D Isohypsibius rusticus sp. nov. (holotype, slide No. 5540). A, Claws of the first pair of legs. B, Claws of the second pair of legs. C, D, Claws of the fourth pair of legs (one lunule is visible: arrow). Scale bar = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/232649/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232650>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. A – C, Isohypsibius gilvus (paratype, slide No. 3571). A, cuticular ornamentation, B, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus. C, Claws of the second and third pair of legs. D, E, Isohypsibius verae (holotype, slide No. 3679). D, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus. E, Claws of the first and second pair of legs. Scale bar = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/232650/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232651>
    dc:description "FIGURE 4. A, Isohypsibius barbarae (paratype slide No. 3678). A, Cuticular undulations are visible. B, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus (paratype, slide 4820). C, Claws of the second pair of legs (holotype, slide 4820). D, Claws of the fourth pair of legs (holotype, slide 4820). The accessory points (arrow) and the lunules are visible. Scale bar = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/232651/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.232652>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. A – E, Isohypsibius zappalai sp. nov. (holotype, slide No. 5551). A B, C, Cuticular ornamentation (A, the anterior portion of the body, B, the posterior portion), and C, shows the tubercles form transverse lines (arrows )). D, Bucco-pharyngeal apparatus and claws of the first pair of legs. E, Claws of the fourth pair of legs (arrow a indicates an accessory point, b indicates a lunule). Scale bar = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/232652/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

